<subSubSection id="6AB59980FFF7FF97FF67FA52AB8A3DEB" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2210CA0BFFF7FF97FF67FA52AB8A3DEB" blockId="1.[151,1437,1508,1751]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">
<emphasis id="10DB1619FFF7FF97FF67FA52A8763EC3" bold="true" box="[151,274,1508,1534]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E5AFB188FFF7FF97FEE9FA52A8C63EC3" authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1893" box="[281,418,1508,1534]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Macrophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="10DB1619FFF7FF97FEE9FA52A8C63EC3" box="[281,418,1508,1534]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">Macrophyes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="E5AFB188FFF7FF97FD24FA52AA4C3EC3" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1903" box="[724,808,1508,1534]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Mesilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="10DB1619FFF7FF97FD24FA52AA4C3EC3" box="[724,808,1508,1534]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">Mesilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having elongated and thin body; long and thin legs; median apophysis on anterior side of the tegulum and a large retromarginal tooth on distal side of chelicerae, but can been distinguished by the laminar ventral tegular projection; a short embolus basally inserted on the tegulum (
<bibRefCitation id="463EB7FAFFF7FF97FF6FF9E6A8EF3D56" author="Brescovit, A. D." box="[159,395,1616,1643]" pageId="1" pageNumber="582" pagination="101 - 106" refId="ref5208" refString="Brescovit, A. D. (1992) Revisao das aranhas do genero Macrophyes O. Pickard-Cambridge, da regiao Neotropical (Araneae, Anyphaenidae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 36, 101 - 106." type="journal article" year="1992">Brescovit 1992: 105</bibRefCitation>
, figs 1−3, 6−11; 1993: 116, figs 1, 2; 
<figureCitation id="BA94D68EFFF7FF97FCB8F9E6AAEE3D57" box="[840,906,1616,1642]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="2.[151,168,1741,1767]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,306,1717]" captionTargetId="figure-76@2.[189,1398,306,1717]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1A−G. Macrophyes sanzi n. sp. Male (MPUJ_ENT 0061936): A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D same, retrolateral view; E same, ventral view. Female (MPUJ_ENT 0061923): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations:A, atrium; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A, B, F: 2mm; C: 1mm; D−E: 0.5mm; F, G: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506500/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">Figs 1</figureCitation>
C−E). Females are characterized by their thin copulatory ducts, anteriorly curved and with small seminal receptacles on medial region; laminar and convergent lateral borders, forming a median, longer than wide atrium, and copulatory openings in anterior position (
<bibRefCitation id="463EB7FAFFF7FF97FADFF92EA86E3DEA" author="Brescovit, A. D." pageId="1" pageNumber="582" pagination="101 - 106" refId="ref5208" refString="Brescovit, A. D. (1992) Revisao das aranhas do genero Macrophyes O. Pickard-Cambridge, da regiao Neotropical (Araneae, Anyphaenidae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 36, 101 - 106." type="journal article" year="1992">Brescovit 1992: 105</bibRefCitation>
, figs 4, 5; 1993: 116, figs 3−6; 
<figureCitation id="BA94D68EFFF7FF97FD99F90AAB863DEB" box="[617,738,1724,1750]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="2.[151,168,1741,1767]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,306,1717]" captionTargetId="figure-76@2.[189,1398,306,1717]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1A−G. Macrophyes sanzi n. sp. Male (MPUJ_ENT 0061936): A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D same, retrolateral view; E same, ventral view. Female (MPUJ_ENT 0061923): B habitus, dorsal view; F epigynum, ventral view; G epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations:A, atrium; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum; VTP, ventral tegular process. Scale bars: A, B, F: 2mm; C: 1mm; D−E: 0.5mm; F, G: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506500/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="582">Figs 1F, G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
